<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-20T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-20T11:36:00-05:00" n="413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 614.119/104</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-20T10:00:00-06:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 22, 12.34
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your September 18, 5 p.m. In an interview yesterday afternoon
                                President <persName corresp="#p_ECM1">Cabrera</persName> assured me
                                that full authority to sell would be <pb facs="0455" n="371" xml:id="pg_371"/> given to the Alien Property Custodian within a
                                few days, and asked me to inform the Department, but not to reveal
                                it otherwise until the decree is published.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>